<TEXT>
a beached baby whale who had followed his 
dying mother onto a north carolina beach has died at sea world 
where officials blamed stress undernourishment and dehydration 
the complications causing the 5foot pygmy sperm whales death 
friday are common symptoms among stranded marine mammals said 
daniel odell research biologist at the orlando tourist 
attractionresearch center where the whale was taken thursday 
tests showed it was on the verge of kidney failure and other 
things it was a very sick little whale said odell who had not 
expected the 140pound animal to survive 
historically baby whales who beach themselves die within days 
one lasted a month at sea world last year older ones survive a 
little longer odell said 
the baby whale dubbed sophia by its rescuers near wilmington 
nc before it was found to be a male beached itself with its 
mother the mother was dying when they were discovered and 
veterinarians killed it 
odell said the usual reason for adult whale beachings is 
congestive heart failure 
</TEXT>
