<TEXT>
a fire broke out in a prison shoe 
factory where more than 100 inmates were working but all of them 
escaped to other parts of the prison unharmed officials said 
there are no injuries that we know of but there was heavy 
damage a lot of smoke said shelly zent department of 
corrections spokeswoman 
she said 133 inmates and five employees were in the ellis 1 unit 
factory at the time of the blaze friday the building is not 
connected to any other prison building 
the inmates were back in their cells she said 
the fire started in a factory storage area on the second floor 
but the cause has not been determined ms zent said 
there are 1971 inmates including death row prisoners at the 
maximumsecurity prison 
inmates work in the factory where nearly all of the boots and 
shoes issued to state prisoners are made 
