befriended by a library worker has left 135000 to the tulsa 
library trust the largest bequest it ever has received 
ethel crate taught high school english for 40 years in tulsa in 
1968 special services librarian gerry hendon began delivering 
books to miss crate at her thirdfloor walkup apartment 
ms hendon said she and miss crate shared a love of books 
ethel was a senior citizen without family ties in the city of 
tulsa ms hendon said thursday when the bequest was announced 
and i guess i fulfilled a need for her 
when miss crate died in 1986 she left the money to be used for 
classical literature and music at the library 
