<TEXT>
congressional negotiators moved a giant step 
closer to final agreement on catastrophic health insurance 
legislation by reaching a tentative compromise on a new medicare 
prescription drug benefit 
rep fortney h stark dcalif said friday he was hopeful that 
resolution of the complicated drug issue by a housesenate working 
group of eight legislators could pave the way for final votes on 
the overall legislation next week 
although several other differences have yet to be worked out in 
the first major expansion of medicare in its 23year history stark 
said they are not likely to be as sticky as the drug benefit 
both the senate and house versions of the underlying legislation 
contained a prescription drug benefit 
however the house version was more expansive and from the 
senate perspective had far fewer controls to keep the potentially 
unpredictable costs of a new program from outstripping revenues 
collected to pay for it 
medicare does not now cover any outpatient drugs except for a 
handful of particularly costly medications such as antirejection 
drugs for transplant recipients 
the compromise being recommended to the full housesenate 
conference committee by the working group calls for the new drug 
benefit to be phased in starting jan 1 1991 
after a 600 deductible is met medicare would pay half the cost 
of any other prescription drugs in 1991 the medicare share still 
after a 600 deductible would rise to 60 percent in 1992 and to 
80 percent in 1993 and thereafter 
in a costcontrol measure pushed by the senate the premiums 
charged beneficiaries to cover the new drug benefit would be 
indexed each year to cover the cost of the program and to keep a 
special drug payment trust fund solvent 
in the first two years of the program until the indexing 
mechanism could be put in full force the secretary of the 
department of health and human would have broad powers to keep 
costs within projected income 
thereafter the indexing feature would cover additional costs 
the initial level of those premiums and details of the indexing 
are to be worked out in subsequent negotiations of the full 
conference committee 
although the full conference also has several other differences 
to resolve there is broad support for the underlying legislation 
which passed both houses of congress overwhelmingly 
administration sources have indicated president reagan whose 
original proposal did not contain a prescription drug benefit is 
likely to sign the measure if it has adequate safeguards to protect 
against runaway drug costs 
the basic legislation does not make provisions for basic 
longterm nursing home care under medicare but would shield 
medicare beneficiaries against financially crippling outofpocket 
doctor and hospital bills 
while the cap is one of the issues still to be resolved it is 
expected to be between 1043 the latest house offer and 1370 
the latest senate offer medicare would pick up all hospital and 
physician costs for a beneficiary after the cap was met in a given 
year 
medicare now pays full costs for 60 days of a hospital stay in a 
given year minus a firstday deductible and pays 80 percent of 
doctor bills no matter how high they range 
on the cost side the major disagreement is how to distribute 
the additional costs medicare enrollees will have to pay both a 
flat monthly fee that will be imposed on all and a socalled 
supplemental premium that is tantamount to an income tax surcharge 
for the estimated 60 percent of medicare recipients with enough 
income to make them subject to federal income taxes 
