stubbornrooted mesquite trees 
at about 830 pm on may 22 1987 the twister dipped from the 
clouds near the davis mountains six miles to the south and skipped 
across the fields before slamming into the community center during 
a preschool graduation ceremony the community center was destroyed 
along with 61 houses the catholic church the candelas familys 
convenience store and pieces of farm machinery 
