after the tornado there were no houses but there were all sorts 
of tv satellite trucks parked up and down the highway 
now new small boxlike houses built by red cross volunteers 
line saragosas streets the new community center boasts a basement 
shelter that can hold up to 300 people a warning siren on a 
30foot pole stands in the centers back yard a new church is 
