be an unemployed politician to run for president hess said 
that was the history of richard nixon in 1968 it was the history 
of jimmy carter in 1976 it was the history of ronald reagan in 
1980 and it was the history of fritz mondale in 1984 
so he has shown us that it is doable thats the important 
thing the conventional wisdom was otherwise hess said 
how well dukakis is able to fulfill his governors duties during 
this time will be more of a state issue than a national one hess 
said adding that massachusetts residents may be less harsh on the 
governor under the circumstances 
the upside of this for the commonwealth hess added is the 
prospect of possibly having your favorite son in the white 
house 
</TEXT>
